abstract: CoolPlanetBiofuels, which received $20 million in the financing round, is developing mobile refineries to turn wood chips, agriculture waste and other biomass into biofuel.
snippet: CoolPlanetBiofuels, which received $20 million in the financing round, is developing mobile refineries to turn wood chips, agriculture waste and other biomass into biofuel.
lead_paragraph: Google Ventures has led a $20 million financing round in CoolPlanetBiofuels, a Southern California start-up that is developing mobile refineries to turn wood chips, agriculture waste and other biomass into biofuels.

headline.main: Google Ventures Leads Financing of Biofuels Start-Up
